A rap concert in Sydney was soured after a violent brawl broke out that saw several people assaulted.

Riot squads were called to the Enmore Theatre in Sydney on Monday night to control thousands of fans who had got out of control while waiting in line for the sold-out concert of US rappers YG and Ty Dolla $ign .

Several arrests were made, with police charging one 24-year-old man with indecently assaulting a person under the age of 16.

