Heavily-armed riot police dispersed about 2500 fans after the concert had finished. 

Images on social media show a heavy police presence speaking to revellers out the front of the concert. 

The Californian rapper YG has been are gaining popularity in America along with a reputation for violence at their concerts and alleged gang affiliations.

In 2013, YG’s single ‘My N****’ peaked at number 19 on the US Billboard hottest 100.

In 2012, YG had a music video shoot for his song ‘I’m A Thug’ shut down by police after reports of shots were fired.

A crowd at the 400 block of W. Spruce St in Compton was cleared from the scene after police closed off the area.

He also had members of the Crips gang arrive at his concert and start a brawl in November 2011. YG is allegedly a member of rival group the Bloods. 

 

 

